    This visual breaks down the Kubernetes Deployment structure into its key components:
The Deployment Hierarchy:
1. Metadata — Names and labels the deployment object itself so you can identify it in your cluster.
2. Spec — The core configuration that tells Kubernetes: "I want 2 replicas of this pod running." This is where you define the desired state.
3. Selector — The critical bridge that tells the deployment which pods belong to it. The matchLabels here (app: my-first-deployment) must exactly match the labels you put on the pods in the template.
4. Template — The blueprint for creating pods. It contains metadata (labels) and a spec (the actual pod definition).
5. Template Metadata — Assigns labels to each pod that gets created. These labels MUST match your selector, or the deployment won't recognize those pods as its own.
6. Pod Spec with Containers — The actual container configuration—which image to run (nginx), what port to expose (80), and resource limits.
Key Flow: The deployment says "I want 2 replicas" → it uses the selector to find pods labeled app: my-first-deployment → if it finds fewer than 2, it uses the template to create new pods with that exact label → each new pod runs the nginx container.
If the template labels don't match the selector labels, Kubernetes gets confused and won't manage those pods correctly. That's why both the selector and template metadata define the same label—it's the glue holding the deployment 
#to apply this yaml kubectl apply -f dep.yml
apiVersion: apps/v1 
kind: Deployment #now we are creating a deployment object
metadata: 
  creationTimestamp: null
  labels:
    app: my-first-deployment
  name: my-first-deployment #this is the name of the deployment object
spec: #this is the specification of the deployment object
  replicas: 2 #this is the number of replicas we want to create for this deployment
  selector:
    matchLabels: #labels
      app: my-first-deployment #both pod will have this label and this is how deployment will know that these pods are belong to this deployment
  strategy: {} #match expression of the deployment strategy
  template: #inside the pod contaner 
    metadata:
      creationTimestamp: null
      labels:
        app: my-first-deployment #with the templatewe are defining same label
    spec: #this is the specification of the pod template
      containers: #in specification we define the contianer
      - image: nginx
        name: nginx
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80
        resources: {}
status: {}
